      • testAfterTwo_Alternative

        public void testAfterTwo_Alternative()
                              throws Throwable
        Same test as testAfterTwo(), but using an alternative writing.

        Here, the dependency of the third operation on the completion of the first two operations is programmed explicitly. In practice this is redundant since the second operation also depends on the completion of the first operation, but it is better to explicitly check.

        Throws:
        Throwable - if thrown during the test
